===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|langage}}, {{m|enm|language}}, from {{der|en|fro|language}}, from {{der|en|VL.|*linguāticum}}, from {{der|en|la|lingua||tongue, speech, language}}, from {{der|en|itc-ola|dingua||tongue}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*dn̥ǵʰwéh₂s||tongue, speech, language}}. 

Displaced native {{noncog|enm|rearde}}, {{m|enm|ȝerearde|t=language}} (from {{noncog|ang|reord|t=language, speech}}), {{cog|enm|londspeche|t=language, national language}} (from {{noncog|ang|*landsprǣċ|t=language, national tongue}}, {{noncog|ang|þēod}} and {{m|ang|þēodisċ|t=language}}, {{noncog|enm|lede}}, {{m|enm|leden|t=language, speech, utterance}} (from {{noncog|ang|lēoden|t=language, national tongue}} > Scottish {{noncog|en|leid|t=language}}).

